<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,726,1003]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">
<specimenCount box="[199,353,762,787]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">
<number box="[199,227,763,787]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="21.0">21</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
were caught at depths between between 
<number box="[831,873,763,787]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="720.0">720</number>
and 
<quantity box="[933,1031,763,787]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.094" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="m" value="1094.0">1,094 m</quantity>
. Length data were available for 
<specimenCount pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">
<number box="[1408,1436,763,787]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="17.0">17</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
ranging from 
<quantity box="[428,575,798,823]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.55" metricValueMax="13.6" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="cm" value="85.5" valueMax="136.0" valueMin="35.0">35 to 136 cm</quantity>
TL. All specimens were identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1099,798,823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Aphanopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="carbo">
<emphasis box="[1003,1099,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">A. carbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, this species can be easily confused with the sympatric 
<taxonomicName box="[548,711,834,859]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Aphanopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[548,711,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">A. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the presence of the latter species in the catches cannot be ruled out. Habitat and Distribution: bathypelagic at depth range 
<quantity box="[867,1017,871,895]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="17.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="m" value="950.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1,700 m</quantity>
, usually 
<quantity box="[1117,1268,871,895]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="m" value="1000.0" valueMax="1300.0" valueMin="700.0">700–1,300 m</quantity>
. It is present at both sides of the North Atlantic Ocean, at least between 
<number box="[801,828,906,931]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="69.0">69</number>
ºN and 
<number box="[916,945,906,931]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="26.0">26</number>
ºN. In the eastern Atlantic Ocean, it occurs from the strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[358,462,942,967]" name="Denmark" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Denmark</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[504,679,942,967]" name="Western Sahara" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">western Sahara</collectingCountry>
, including the Canaries Islands and the Madeira Archipelago and numerous submarine banks and seamounts. Vulnerability: DD (
<collectionCode box="[861,935,979,1003]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">IUCN</collectionCode>
), HHV (FishBase).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1050,1255]" box="[151,878,1050,1075]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">
<taxonomicName authority="Steindachner, 1891" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,643,1050,1075]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Trichiuridae" genus="Benthodesmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simonyi">
<emphasis box="[151,406,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Benthodesmus simonyi</emphasis>
(Steindachner, 
<number box="[581,634,1050,1075]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="1891.0">1891</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
—Simony's frostfish
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,1050,1255]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">
<specimenCount box="[199,353,1086,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">
<number box="[199,227,1086,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="36.0">36</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
were caught at depths between 
<number box="[727,769,1086,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="652.0">652</number>
and 
<specimenCount box="[829,910,1087,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">
<quantity box="[829,906,1087,1111]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.77" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="m" value="877.0">877 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
Length data were available for 
<specimenCount box="[1282,1437,1086,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">
<number box="[1282,1310,1087,1111]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" value="20.0">20</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
ranging from 
<quantity box="[309,462,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.7" metricValueMin="7.3" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="cm" value="95.0" valueMax="117.0" valueMin="73.0">73 to 117 cm</quantity>
TL. Habitat and Distribution: benthopelagic and oceanic at depth range 
<quantity box="[1300,1432,1123,1147]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" unit="m" value="550.0" valueMax="900.0" valueMin="200.0">
200– 
<specimenCount box="[1356,1432,1123,1147]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324" type="generic">900 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
. Distributed on the continental slope and underwater rises; juveniles are mesopelagic. Both sides of the North Atlantic, off Newfoundland (
<collectingCountry box="[480,569,1194,1219]" name="Canada" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Canada</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[590,695,1194,1219]" name="Bermuda" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Bermuda</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry box="[770,863,1194,1219]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">England</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[880,941,1195,1219]" name="United States of America" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">USA</collectingCountry>
), Middle Atlantic Ridges, 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1328,1194,1219]" name="Iceland" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Iceland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1341,1432,1195,1219]" name="Norway" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Norway</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,249,1230,1255]" name="Portugal" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, Madeira, and Canary Islands. Vulnerability: DD (
<collectionCode box="[813,887,1231,1255]" pageId="31" pageNumber="324">IUCN</collectionCode>
), HV (FishBase).
</paragraph>
